21/03/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- An agreement providing increased OSCE support for Kosovo human rights projects was sealed between Prime Minister Agim Ceku and OSCE Ambassador Werner Wendt in Pristina on Monday (20 March). The agreement envisions the creation of a joint Central Human Rights Advisory Unit, staffed by senior human rights advisers, to work within select Kosovo ministries to provide daily assistance. 
In other news, former Kosovo Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj, provisionally released from The Hague until his trial for war crimes begins, met on Monday with UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen. They discussed implementation of internationally set standards in the province and improvement of minority rights. It was Haradinaj's first public appearance since the tribunal's recent decision to allow him to participate in political activities again. (OSCE Web site, KosovaLive, Tanjug - 20/03/06)
